<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, shrink-to-fit=no" />
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge" />
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css" />
    <title>WW Insertion Sort</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div id="app">
      <div class="container-fluid mt-5">
        <div class="row content">
          <div class="col-sm-2 "></div>
          <div class="col-sm-8 ">
            <div class="jumbotron text-center">
              <h1>âš™ Web Worker Insertion Sort</h1>
              <p class="lead mr-5 ml-5">
                An implementation of insertion sort algorithm performed by Web Workers, which will also receive random
                number each X a predefined interval in milliseconds.
              </p>
              <p class="lead">
                We are expecting a stable sorting time average, with an array size of <strong>100K</strong> no matter
                what the interval
                <strong>X</strong>
                is. So let's check together!
              </p>
              <p class="lead">
                ðŸ’¡
                <small>
                  What is mesuremnt of a <strong>'Stable'</strong> message time processing, especially with different
                  factors can have an effect on the processing time?! in this application we consider a time as an
                  <strong>'Unstable'</strong> message processing time if it is longer than
                  <strong>13 milliseconds. </strong></small
                >
                <a href="http://news.mit.edu/2014/in-the-blink-of-an-eye-0116" target="_blank">
                  Why?? maybe this article can explain a bit maybe this article can explain a bit!</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-2"></div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-sm-2 "></div>
          <div class="col-sm-8 ">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-sm-8">
                <div id="configurationForm" class="form-group">
                  <h2>Configuration panel</h2>
                  <hr />
                  <form>
                    <label for="arraySizeInput">Array size</label>
                    <input
                      type="number"
                      class="form-control"
                      id="arraySizeInput"
                      value="100000"
                      placeholder="the size of the array which will be sorted"
                    />
                    <small class="form-text text-muted"></small>
                    <label for="intervalInput">The Interval of adding number to the array</label>
                    <input
                      type="number"
                      class="form-control"
                      id="intervalInput"
                      value="1"
                      placeholder="interval in milliseconds"
                    />
                    <small class="form-text text-muted"></small>
                    <br />
                    <button id="startButton" class="btn btn-warning btn-block form-control" type="submit">Start</button>
                  </form>
                  <hr />
                  <div id="feedbackBox"></div>
                  <div id="reportBox"></div>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="col-sm-4">
                <h2>Messages logs</h2>
                <hr />
                <div id="message-log-list" class="list-group message-list">
                  <div class="log"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="logs-info mt-3 alert alert-light text-small">
                  <p>
                    Please note that there are 4 message types
                    <strong>[ RESET, SET_DATA, START_SORT, DONE ]</strong> that will be <strong>always</strong> logged
                    as they indicate the initilizing and termintaing of the sorting process. The rest of the messages
                    will be logged if their <strong>processing time i > 13ms.</strong> otherwise they are considered as
                    <strong>'real-time'</strong> message won't be logged
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-sm-2 "></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="main.bundle.js"></script>
  </body>
</html>
